THOUGHT: The crash is due to improveShuffleKindFromMask calling IR helpers that assert when the shuffle mask contains poison/undef elements (negative indices). I will add a defensive early-return in improveShuffleKindFromMask to skip refinement when any mask element is negative, which prevents assertions while keeping correctness. Then I will submit the patch.

```bash
python3 - << 'PY' && submit-patch
import sys, pathlib
p = pathlib.Path("llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/BasicTTIImpl.h")
s = p.read_text()
sig = "improveShuffleKindFromMask("
idx = s.find(sig)
if idx == -1:
    print("Signature not found", file=sys.stderr)
    sys.exit(1)
brace_idx = s.find("{", idx)
if brace_idx == -1:
    print("Opening brace not found", file=sys.stderr)
    sys.exit(1)
guard = """\
    // Avoid refining shuffle kind when mask contains poison/undef elements.
    // Negative indices can trigger assertions in IR helpers.
    for (int M : Mask) {
      if (M < 0)
        return SK;
    }
"""
# Avoid duplicate insertion
if guard in s:
    print("Guard already present")
else:
    s = s[:brace_idx+1] + "\n" + guard + s[brace_idx+1:]
    p.write_text(s)
print("Patched BasicTTIImpl.h")
PY
```

